President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Arizona due to severe winter storms and flooding that occurred from January 18-22, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Mark A. Neveau has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.